{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend statutory bereavement leave to pregnancy loss before 24 weeks",
        "additional_details": "We lost our daughter at 23 weeks gestation and although my employer was fantastic many aren\u2019t. Two weeks is not enough time to recover and grieve but it is certainly a start.",
        "background": "Currently if you lose a baby after 24 weeks you are as a minimum entitled to statutory maternity leave. As these same rights aren\u2019t afforded before 24 weeks 2 weeks full pay should be provided as an absolute minimum to parents who have suffered the death of a baby at any stage of pregnancy.",
